bug.short_desc: Series render is not correct when value is zero.

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 86809 screenshot
Series render is not correct.
build version: 2.3.0 v20080114-0800
steps to reproduce: 1. New a script dataset,with three columns: category(a,b,c,d,e),value(25.4,35.8,15.2,5.9,20.6),group(goup1,group2,group2,goup2,group3,group3) 2. Insert a bar chart to report, select group as category series, select value as value series. Enable the group on Category, group type: Text, Unit: String, Interval: 1. 3. Add aggregation: Is-Bottom-Percent, Percentage as 2. 4. Check the Live Preview.
Expected result: As Y Axis scale is -1, 0, 1, so bar should be drawn to show the value is 1.
Actual result: No bar is drawn, please see attached screenshot.
Sorry, the expected result should be: As Y Axis scale is -1, 0, 1, so bar should be drawn to show the value is 0.
It's not a bug, the result is correct.
